# Claude OS Runtime (Cursor)

## Read first

- **`CLAUDE.md`** — project policy and entry for Claude Code–aligned work.
- **`.claude/session-state.md`** — live branch, risks, decisions, next steps.
- **`.claude/workflow-manifest.json`** — progressive delivery gates.
- **`.claude/os-capabilities.json`** — what automation and routing are allowed.

Also keep **`AGENTS.md`** (repo root) aligned: it is the thin cross-tool contract for Codex/Cursor/others.

## Behaviour

- Prefer **lower risk and lower cost** paths when multiple options exist.
- Prefer **`pwsh .claude/scripts/*.ps1`** for OS flows instead of inventing parallel scripts.
- **Close sessions** with **`session-digest`** when finishing meaningful work (see `AGENTS.md` for the example invocation).

## Destructive or high-blast-radius actions

Do **not** run destructive git, filesystem, permission, CI, security, or production changes without **human approval required**.

## Single runtime

Operational truth lives only under **`.claude/`**. Do not create a parallel OS root (e.g. `.cursor-os/`).
